body:
Wassup guys/girls/aliens/dogs/cats, {{summoner:21}} 

Is there any way to reset/lower your ranking(MMR) im plat IV atm?

Because the last year i havent been able to play any serious or alot to keep my platinum ranking and skills up because of my new job.
But one thing i noticed is that i feed alot of my games and that i cant win my lanes anymore..... like litteraly zero for the last 40 games.
Of course sometimes you get a game where you can catch some kills later on in the game camping under tower 24/7...... but i dont want that with every game... my mind isn't made anymore to tryhard every game and just want to have my MMR lowered down...

Maybe it is the luck but my team always carries me through so its not that i start losing rank XD haha
And being yelled at every single game that i can get cancer, fuck my mother, etc im a bit done with as well (even though i know thats simply the league community).{{summoner:14}} 
I always play against diamonds and platinums (even on normals), which im not worth playing against anymore... im lucky if i can win versus a legit silver player.
And before these people are like "go put more time in it then" no... too bad my job asks too much time of me already :| but it is a fun game so not thinking of uninstalling/leaving it.

So if you guys have any tips or hints by getting me back to silver or even bronze, i dont care, so i can stop playing ranked and just play normals (staying off ranked takes too long to lower at this point) but so my MMR comes to a point where i get matched up with people of my own level.

Thanks and regards,

ItsMike{{summoner:7}} 
{{sticker:slayer-pantheon-thumbs}}
